NOTE: Pursuant to Fed. Cir. R. 47.6, this order is not citable as precedent. It is a public order.

In re AEROSPACE OPTICS, INC. No. 2006-1526. United States Court of Appeals, Federal Circuit. Oct. 12, 2006.

ORDER

Upon consideration of Aerospace Optics, Inc.’s unopposed motion to voluntarily dismiss its appeal,

IT IS ORDERED THAT:

(1) The motion is granted.

(2) Each side shall bear its own costs.
